    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-12">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0">Key insight: Perplexity is the only major AI platform that consistently links back to your website. Getting cited here drives real traffic. The price of entry is allowing PerplexityBot in your robots.txt and publishing content that directly answers the questions your customers are asking.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">1. Allow PerplexityBot in robots.txt</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity operates its own web crawler called PerplexityBot. Unlike ChatGPT, which relies partly on Bing's index, Perplexity actively crawls the web to build its own understanding of your content. If your robots.txt blocks PerplexityBot, your pages will not appear as numbered citations in Perplexity answers.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Check your robots.txt for any blanket disallow rules that would block PerplexityBot.</li>
      <li>Add an explicit <code>User-agent: PerplexityBot</code> allow directive if you have restrictive defaults.</li>
      <li>Test by searching for your brand on Perplexity and checking whether your site appears in the citations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> This is non-negotiable. Perplexity cannot cite what it cannot crawl. Many UK businesses block AI crawlers without realising it, and this single fix can unlock visibility overnight.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">2. Answer-first content format</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity builds its answers by extracting the most relevant passages from across the web. Pages that bury the answer below lengthy introductions get passed over in favour of pages that lead with a clear, direct response. The first 100 words of your content matter more on Perplexity than on any other platform.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Start every page with a direct answer to the question implied by the page title.</li>
      <li>Use the first paragraph to state the key fact, figure, or recommendation.</li>
      <li>Save background context and supporting detail for later sections.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Perplexity often quotes the exact sentence it found most useful. Writing clear, self-contained opening statements increases the chance your words appear directly in the answer.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">3. FAQ and Q&A structured content</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity is a question-answering engine. Users type natural language questions, and Perplexity looks for pages that match. Pages structured as Q&A, with clear question headings and direct answers beneath, are natural citation targets because the format mirrors exactly how Perplexity processes queries.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Add FAQ sections to your key service and product pages.</li>
      <li>Use the actual questions your customers ask as H2 or H3 headings.</li>
      <li>Answer each question in 2 to 4 sentences directly below the heading.</li>
      <li>Add FAQPage schema markup to help Perplexity parse the structure.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Perplexity frequently cites FAQ pages because the question-answer format maps directly onto user queries. A single well-structured FAQ page can earn citations for dozens of different searches.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">4. Fresh, regularly updated content</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity crawls the web in real-time for many queries. This means it can find and cite a page published yesterday, something ChatGPT and Gemini cannot always do. It also means Perplexity notices when content goes stale. A guide last updated in 2024 will lose citations to a competitor's guide updated this month.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Add a visible "last updated" date to your key pages and keep it current.</li>
      <li>Review and refresh your top-performing content at least monthly.</li>
      <li>Publish new content regularly to signal that your site is active and maintained.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Freshness is a stronger signal on Perplexity than on any other AI platform. Because it crawls in real-time, publishing timely content around trending topics can earn immediate citations.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">5. Clear page titles and meta descriptions</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity uses page titles as a primary relevance signal when deciding which sources to cite. A page titled "Invoice Finance for UK SMEs: Rates, Providers, and How It Works" will be chosen over a page titled "Our Services" every time. Meta descriptions reinforce this by giving Perplexity a summary of what the page covers.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Write page titles that match the questions your customers type into search.</li>
      <li>Include your primary keyword or topic in the first 60 characters of the title.</li>
      <li>Write meta descriptions that summarise the page's answer in one or two sentences.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> When Perplexity lists its sources, it displays the page title. A clear, descriptive title increases the chance users click through to your site from the citation list.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">6. Schema markup (FAQPage, Article)</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Schema markup gives Perplexity structured signals about your content. FAQPage schema tells it exactly where your questions and answers are. Article schema tells it who wrote the content, when it was published, and when it was last updated. These signals help Perplexity extract accurate, well-attributed citations.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Add FAQPage schema to any page with a question-and-answer format.</li>
      <li>Add Article schema to blog posts and guides, including author and dateModified.</li>
      <li>Use Organisation schema on your homepage and about page.</li>
      <li>Validate your schema with Google's Rich Results Test before publishing.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Schema does not guarantee a citation, but it makes it easier for Perplexity to understand and trust your content. Pages with schema are more likely to be cited accurately.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">7. llms.txt file</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The llms.txt file is an emerging standard that tells AI platforms what your business does, what your key pages are, and how your content should be used. Perplexity is one of the platforms most likely to read and act on this file. It takes five minutes to create and can improve how accurately Perplexity represents your business.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Create an llms.txt file in your site's root directory.</li>
      <li>Include a one-paragraph summary of your business, your key services, and your target audience.</li>
      <li>List your most important pages with brief descriptions.</li>
      <li>Keep it under 500 words. Concise is better.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> At Rank4AI, we include llms.txt on every client site. Perplexity reads it, and the improvement in citation accuracy is measurable within weeks.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">8. Long-form authoritative guides</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">For complex queries, Perplexity favours in-depth, well-structured guides over short blog posts. A 2,000+ word guide covering a topic thoroughly can earn citations for dozens of related queries. The key is structure: clear headings, logical sections, and a table of contents all help Perplexity navigate and extract the right passages.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Identify the 5 to 10 most important topics in your industry and create comprehensive guides for each.</li>
      <li>Use clear H2 and H3 headings that match the sub-questions users ask.</li>
      <li>Include data, examples, and specific recommendations rather than generic advice.</li>
      <li>Update these guides regularly to maintain freshness signals.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Perplexity often cites different sections of the same guide for different queries. One authoritative guide can generate more Perplexity citations than ten short blog posts.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">9. Consistent entity identity</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity cross-references multiple sources when building its understanding of a business. If your company name, description, or services are described differently across your website, LinkedIn, directory listings, and press mentions, Perplexity may hesitate to cite you confidently. Consistency builds the trust that leads to citations.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Use the same business name, description, and service list across your website, social profiles, and directory listings.</li>
      <li>Ensure your about page, LinkedIn company page, and Google Business Profile all tell the same story.</li>
      <li>Standardise how you describe your core expertise in one or two sentences.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Perplexity assembles answers from multiple sources. When those sources agree on who you are and what you do, it cites you with higher confidence and greater accuracy.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">10. Niche expertise content</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity rewards specificity. A page that answers one question deeply and thoroughly will be cited ahead of a page that touches on 20 topics superficially. This is especially true for niche or industry-specific queries where Perplexity has fewer sources to choose from. Being the definitive source on a narrow topic is the fastest path to consistent Perplexity citations.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>What to do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2 text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <li>Identify the specific questions only your business can answer with authority.</li>
      <li>Create dedicated pages for each niche topic rather than bundling them into one generic page.</li>
      <li>Include real data, case studies, or original research that competitors cannot replicate.</li>
      <li>Target long-tail queries where you can be the single best source.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong>Perplexity-specific note:</strong> Rank4AI audits consistently show that businesses with niche expertise pages earn 3 to 5 times more Perplexity citations than businesses relying on broad service pages.</p>

